The article is a statement by the President on the 70th anniversary of the end of World War II in the Pacific. The President pays tribute to the American servicemen and women who fought in the Pacific and the allied forces they served with. He also remembers the prisoners of war and honors the sacrifice of over 100,000 U.S. service members who died in the Pacific theater. The President expresses gratitude to all the Americans who served in World War II and acknowledges that our freedom today is because of their brave service. The article also highlights the reconciliation and strong relationship between the United States and Japan over the past 70 years and expresses confidence in the deepening of this partnership in the future.